This paper deals with decision making using predictive models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of strategic behavior on decision making, which falls under game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The use of optimal transport theory to characterize changes in feature distribution is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and mathematical optimization (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of decision making on individuals and society, which is related to computer ethics (cs.CE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
